FBIS4-34775 "drlat122_b_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-122 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Government Establishes Visa Requirement for Foreigners Government Establishes Visa Requirement for Foreigners PA2406023694 Paris AFP in Spanish 0145 GMT 24 Jun 94 PA2406023694 Paris AFP Spanish BFN [Text] Port-au-Prince, 23 Jun (AFP) -- This Thursday, the provisional government of President Emile Jonassaint (not recognized by the international community) established a visa requirement for foreign citizens whose countries demand visas from Haitian citizens. This measure particularly affects U.S. and Canadian citizens, who until now did not need visas to enter Haiti. A government communique stated that a $50 tax will also be required of foreigners entering Haiti. Foreigners will be able to obtain visas at ports and airports in the country.
